WEBVTT

00:01.702 --> 00:03.736
[eerie music builds]

00:03.738 --> 00:05.804
¶¶

00:19.253 --> 00:22.354
[unintelligible radio talk]

00:29.463 --> 00:31.697
[radio talk continues]

01:03.564 --> 01:05.497
[car engine stops]

01:07.301 --> 01:09.635
[birds chirping]

01:34.929 --> 01:36.795
[knocking on door]

01:39.900 --> 01:41.567
- Hello?

01:48.742 --> 01:50.709
[door creaks]

02:02.823 --> 02:06.024
[flies buzzing]

02:11.632 --> 02:13.365
[grunts in disgust]

02:21.509 --> 02:23.575
[flies buzzing]

02:42.496 --> 02:44.563
[distant child coughing]

02:45.966 --> 02:47.633
Hello?

02:48.435 --> 02:49.801
[eerie music builds]

02:49.803 --> 02:51.870
¶¶

03:12.059 --> 03:13.725
Hello.

03:16.030 --> 03:17.863
- Mommy.

03:19.934 --> 03:21.667
Mommy.

03:26.440 --> 03:28.440
Mommy!

03:29.510 --> 03:31.410
- You're safe.

03:32.546 --> 03:34.079
Come on.

03:34.815 --> 03:36.481
- That's a girl.

03:36.617 --> 03:38.383
- Mommy.

03:40.854 --> 03:42.754
Mommy.

03:44.658 --> 03:45.958
[cries]
Mommy.

03:45.960 --> 03:47.693
- Okay, now.

03:47.695 --> 03:49.428
[cries]
- Mommy!

03:49.430 --> 03:52.064
- I know, baby.
I know.

03:55.736 --> 03:57.769
[music continues]

03:57.771 --> 03:59.938
¶¶

04:03.711 --> 04:06.511
[birds chirping]

04:21.929 --> 04:23.996
[pensive music]

04:23.998 --> 04:26.164
¶¶

05:00.534 --> 05:01.833
[bird chirps]

05:09.777 --> 05:11.209
[bird chirps]

05:14.982 --> 05:16.615
[door closes]

05:20.587 --> 05:22.220
[bird chirps]

05:28.562 --> 05:29.728
[recorder beeps]

05:30.097 --> 05:31.663
- Good morning.

05:32.199 --> 05:33.832
I'm Dr. Jackie Deluce.

05:33.834 --> 05:36.601
I'll be in charge of your
therapy from here on out.

05:40.974 --> 05:43.108
How long have you been
out of intensive care?

05:50.551 --> 05:52.217
- Nine days.

05:53.620 --> 05:55.287
- And how're you feeling?

06:00.561 --> 06:02.594
Well, I know one thing,
I know you gotta be sick

06:02.596 --> 06:04.996
of people asking you
questions, yeah?

06:07.234 --> 06:09.935
Sick of being held
against your will, too?

06:11.772 --> 06:13.572
You're on clozapine.

06:13.574 --> 06:14.840
And you know
you need to take that

06:14.842 --> 06:16.708
even if you're feeling better?

06:16.710 --> 06:18.176
- I know.

06:18.946 --> 06:20.312
- Are you feeling better?

06:20.981 --> 06:22.280
- Yes.

06:22.616 --> 06:24.116
- Are you hearing anything

06:24.118 --> 06:28.987
or seeing anything
out of the ordinary?

06:28.989 --> 06:31.289
Anything that
shouldn't be there.
- Nope.

06:34.061 --> 06:35.594
- So why are you here?

06:39.066 --> 06:40.516
You don't belong here?

06:40.517 --> 06:41.967
It's all some big mistake,
something like that?

06:41.969 --> 06:43.668
[softly]
- Fuck you.

06:44.772 --> 06:47.906
- You wanna leave,
I get it.

06:47.908 --> 06:49.641
I'm not the one
forcing you to stay.

06:49.643 --> 06:51.810
I'm the one
who gets you out.

06:52.279 --> 06:53.678
But in order to help you,

06:53.680 --> 06:56.281
I need to be sure
you really are okay,

06:56.283 --> 07:00.085
no longer a threat to yourself
or anyone else, Sybil.

07:02.222 --> 07:04.589
May I call you Sybil?

07:04.591 --> 07:07.325
- Just how do you
determine that exactly?

07:07.327 --> 07:09.094
What sort of calculations
do you run

07:09.096 --> 07:11.997
to see whether I can
get out of here or not, hmm?

07:12.966 --> 07:16.001
What the fuck could you
possibly know about me?

07:18.038 --> 07:20.372
- I know you lost your baby.

07:22.109 --> 07:24.142
You wanna talk about that?

07:27.648 --> 07:30.348
- I didn't lose my baby.

07:35.222 --> 07:37.823
My baby was taken.

07:40.928 --> 07:43.228
- Why don't you come
tell me about it?

08:00.180 --> 08:02.247
- [Sybil]<i> I was eight months</i>
<i> pregnant.</i>

08:05.085 --> 08:07.185
They drugged me.

08:09.022 --> 08:13.391
Took me to a room underground,
an operating room.

08:15.796 --> 08:17.696
Cut me open.

08:18.699 --> 08:20.398
And when I woke up...

08:22.903 --> 08:25.070
he wasn't in me anymore.

08:31.245 --> 08:33.979
- How long had you been off
your medications?

08:34.348 --> 08:37.015
- Two weeks, about that.
Don't do that.

08:37.885 --> 08:40.218
- I'm just eliminating
variables.

08:40.220 --> 08:42.821
One of those variables
is your medical history--
- Medical history

08:42.823 --> 08:44.923
of difficulty distinguishing
between what is real

08:44.925 --> 08:47.092
and what is imaginary.

08:48.161 --> 08:49.895
- Yes.

08:50.364 --> 08:52.197
- I was pregnant.

08:54.301 --> 08:56.434
I had to stop.

08:58.205 --> 09:01.373
- Did you get pregnant before
or after your mother died?

09:02.309 --> 09:04.042
- After.

09:06.980 --> 09:09.147
Katherine died
about a year ago.

09:09.983 --> 09:11.483
She was killed in her car.

09:12.986 --> 09:14.786
- She was killed?

09:15.122 --> 09:16.788
[bird chirps]

09:18.492 --> 09:21.126
When did Katherine adopt you?

09:21.128 --> 09:22.727
- When I was 16.

09:22.729 --> 09:24.396
It's all in the file,
I'm sure.

09:24.398 --> 09:26.498
- Well, I've read your file,

09:26.500 --> 09:29.401
I'd like to hear you
tell your own story.

09:32.940 --> 09:34.806
- Okay.

09:35.809 --> 09:37.475
[coughs]
Um...

09:38.345 --> 09:40.245
Katherine was a case manager

09:40.247 --> 09:43.148
for the Department of Health
and Human Services.

09:45.352 --> 09:48.286
Her office got a call,
anonymous tip,

09:48.288 --> 09:51.523
from this woman who said
her baby was in danger.

09:53.293 --> 09:56.761
I guess I wasn't on top
of the stack but, uh,

09:56.763 --> 09:59.864
eventually Katherine
was sent out to investigate.

10:01.335 --> 10:04.436
I had been alone
for three days, dehydrated,

10:04.438 --> 10:06.504
severe rash.

10:07.407 --> 10:09.808
There were no birth records.

10:10.811 --> 10:13.144
That's all I know.

10:17.818 --> 10:20.952
Early childhood trauma.
You should jot that down.

10:30.197 --> 10:32.497
She eventually adopted me.

10:35.335 --> 10:37.869
Katherine was always
trying to protect me.

10:40.273 --> 10:42.407
She and Dr Morales.

10:44.811 --> 10:46.578
- [Dr. Deluce]<i> Dr. Morales?</i>

10:50.984 --> 10:52.550
- What are you drawing?

10:52.552 --> 10:54.986
- Bad people.

10:56.256 --> 10:58.056
- Bad people?

10:58.358 --> 11:02.160
- Don't want bad men
to get me.

11:11.238 --> 11:14.973
- Did you know that
there's a special place?

11:14.975 --> 11:18.109
A place that's just for you

11:18.111 --> 11:20.178
that no bad people
can get you.

11:21.581 --> 11:23.915
A place where nobody
can get in or out

11:23.917 --> 11:25.450
unless you say so.

11:28.522 --> 11:31.589
You get to decide
where that place is.

11:33.126 --> 11:35.326
Do you wanna go find
that place right now?

11:52.979 --> 11:55.113
[light piano music]

11:55.115 --> 11:56.648
¶¶

11:56.650 --> 11:59.084
Is this your safe place?

12:04.891 --> 12:07.358
- [Sybil]<i> He was always</i>
<i> trying to protect me.</i>

12:08.361 --> 12:10.495
- From the people
who took your baby?

12:11.498 --> 12:13.598
Same people that
killed Katherine?

12:13.600 --> 12:15.467
- You're not listening.

12:15.936 --> 12:16.668
- I'm listening.

12:16.670 --> 12:18.470
- You're dismissing.

12:18.472 --> 12:22.140
You're asking questions based
on a preconceived analysis.

12:23.310 --> 12:25.009
- Two events.

12:25.011 --> 12:26.911
Your pregnancy
and your mother's death

12:26.913 --> 12:29.080
both happening
at the same time.

12:29.249 --> 12:30.582
That's relevant.

12:30.584 --> 12:32.917
- I don't need
another therapist.

12:32.919 --> 12:34.252
- What'd you need?

12:37.624 --> 12:39.457
- I need to leave.

12:39.458 --> 12:41.291
- You think I can just tell the
administration to let you out.

12:41.294 --> 12:43.294
That's not how this works.

12:44.164 --> 12:46.397
Someone has to
present your case.

12:48.668 --> 12:50.668
[inhales]
That person is me.

13:04.684 --> 13:07.685
- I got pregnant the night
of my mother's funeral.

13:19.065 --> 13:20.565
- Excuse me, Miss Warren?

13:20.567 --> 13:21.599
Very sorry,

13:21.601 --> 13:24.135
we need to collect
the service now.

13:24.137 --> 13:25.737
- Okay.
- Thank you.

13:27.107 --> 13:29.140
[faint organ music]

13:29.142 --> 13:31.276
¶¶

13:37.517 --> 13:40.018
[door opening]

13:49.429 --> 13:50.762
- I think I missed it.

13:51.464 --> 13:53.131
The service,
it looks like I missed it.

13:53.133 --> 13:55.200
My flight was delayed,
I wanted to make it.

13:55.702 --> 13:59.137
- Uh, yeah, it ended
a few minutes ago.

14:01.107 --> 14:04.375
- I'm s-- I'm sorry,
I'm-- I'm David Holyfield.

14:04.377 --> 14:06.110
- Sybil Warren.

14:06.379 --> 14:08.513
- I know,
it's good to meet you.

14:08.515 --> 14:10.181
My family funded
Katherine Warren's

14:10.183 --> 14:12.050
non-profit for years, so...

14:12.052 --> 14:14.118
I, um...

14:14.120 --> 14:16.421
I really wanted to be here today
but I thought I'd...

14:16.423 --> 14:18.590
thought I'd take a second
and introduce myself.

14:19.259 --> 14:23.127
- Uh, well, um,
thank you for that.
- Yeah.

14:23.129 --> 14:25.029
- I know it meant
a lot to her.

14:25.031 --> 14:27.065
Everyone's at the reception.

14:27.534 --> 14:29.067
- Oh, okay.

14:33.506 --> 14:34.656
Are you gonna go?

14:34.657 --> 14:35.807
[nervous chuckle]
- I'm sorry.
It's been a hell of a day.

14:35.809 --> 14:37.442
- I can only imagine.

14:37.444 --> 14:39.677
- I don't like crowds
so I'm just...

14:39.679 --> 14:41.479
- Um...

14:42.549 --> 14:45.383
[laughs]
Do you want to get a coffee
or something?

14:47.420 --> 14:49.187
[laughs]
- No...

14:49.189 --> 14:52.390
- I'm sorry I don't mean
to make this weird but I, uh...

14:52.392 --> 14:54.225
- That'd be nice.

14:54.227 --> 14:56.327
I could use the company.

14:56.329 --> 14:58.129
- Okay, great.

14:59.065 --> 15:01.199
- [Sybil]<i> I felt drawn to him.</i>

15:05.138 --> 15:06.821
- You were grieving.

15:06.822 --> 15:08.505
- Yes, but I wasn't
feeling grief.

15:09.809 --> 15:11.376
- [Dr. Deluce]<i> What were</i>
<i> you feeling?</i>

15:16.516 --> 15:18.783
- [Sybil]<i> True isolation.</i>

15:20.086 --> 15:21.853
[light piano music]

15:21.855 --> 15:24.255
¶¶

16:28.154 --> 16:30.455
<i> I needed to be touched.</i>

16:31.691 --> 16:34.726
<i> I needed to feel the skin</i>
<i> of another human being</i>

16:34.728 --> 16:36.794
<i> pressed against mine.</i>

16:37.397 --> 16:39.731
I needed to feel their warmth.

16:39.733 --> 16:43.234
His heat, his heart
beating against mine.

16:44.504 --> 16:46.571
[dramatic music builds]

16:46.573 --> 16:48.573
¶¶

17:48.568 --> 17:50.635
[door opens/closes]

18:06.786 --> 18:08.820
- [Dr. Deluce]<i> You thought</i>
<i> he'd abandoned you.</i>

18:10.256 --> 18:11.923
<i> But he came back.</i>

18:13.393 --> 18:15.259
- [Sybil]<i> Yeah.</i>

18:16.496 --> 18:18.796
Young grieving woman,
no family, no friends,

18:18.798 --> 18:21.365
compensates for a lack
of a sense of belonging

18:21.367 --> 18:22.733
by fucking some stranger.

18:22.735 --> 18:24.569
You should write that down.

18:24.571 --> 18:26.771
- Or maybe he
brought you to life?

18:27.507 --> 18:29.040
You fell in love.

18:29.909 --> 18:33.377
- He was the first time
I remember not feeling alone.

18:34.914 --> 18:37.348
<i> Like...</i>

18:37.350 --> 18:39.016
<i> we belonged together.</i>

18:45.692 --> 18:47.358
<i> Even then he was,</i>

18:47.360 --> 18:51.362
<i> I guess, the idea of</i>
<i> the possibility of family.</i>

18:52.799 --> 18:54.832
<i> A real family.</i>

18:56.069 --> 18:58.936
- [Dr. Deluce]<i> What did his</i>
<i> family think of you?</i>

18:58.938 --> 19:01.639
- [Sybil]<i> They didn't know</i>
<i> about me, not yet.</i>

19:02.408 --> 19:03.908
- [Dr. Deluce]<i> How about</i>
<i> his friends?</i>

19:03.910 --> 19:06.010
- [Sybil]<i> He didn't have</i>
<i> any friends.</i>

19:06.846 --> 19:07.879
<i> I mean, I didn't either.</i>

19:07.881 --> 19:10.081
<i> We were just two loners,</i>

19:10.083 --> 19:12.884
<i> we didn't need anybody else,</i>
<i> we had each other.</i>

19:14.020 --> 19:16.487
<i> It was just the two of us.</i>

19:25.865 --> 19:27.899
I'm pregnant.

19:28.835 --> 19:30.635
- You're pregnant?

19:31.771 --> 19:33.871
- [Sybil]<i> He made me feel</i>
<i> like I was at the center</i>

19:33.873 --> 19:35.806
<i> of the universe.</i>

19:36.609 --> 19:39.377
<i> I remember the day</i>
<i> he proposed to me.</i>

19:42.749 --> 19:44.415
<i> It was like a dream.</i>

19:45.985 --> 19:47.552
<i> Like time stopped.</i>

19:48.488 --> 19:50.388
- I didn't expect this.

19:53.660 --> 19:56.527
- I never expected
to fall in love either.

20:06.005 --> 20:07.605
What?

20:08.841 --> 20:11.442
- Nothing.
Just...

20:15.481 --> 20:17.915
- [Sybil]<i> I didn't want my baby</i>
<i> to end up like me.</i>

20:17.917 --> 20:20.985
- Schizophrenia has a strong
hereditary component--

20:20.987 --> 20:22.820
- You have a one
in ten chance.

20:25.491 --> 20:26.991
- What did you tell him?

20:27.527 --> 20:28.759
- All of it.

20:28.761 --> 20:30.895
I told him my real secret.

20:30.897 --> 20:32.496
- Your secret?

20:34.033 --> 20:36.434
- The voices,
the visions.

20:38.805 --> 20:40.738
They're real, you know.

20:42.675 --> 20:46.110
Suddenly awake and asleep
at the same time.

20:47.013 --> 20:49.981
Like a nightmare and I
can hear their thoughts.

20:50.917 --> 20:52.917
I have flashes
of what they want,

20:52.919 --> 20:54.585
what they need.

20:55.421 --> 20:56.787
And what they're scared of.

20:56.789 --> 20:59.123
- Is it like you see
their aura

20:59.125 --> 21:01.692
or their mood
or is it like empathy?

21:01.694 --> 21:03.527
- It's physical.

21:04.530 --> 21:06.063
It's very real.

21:07.066 --> 21:08.599
- Okay.

21:10.737 --> 21:15.773
Have you ever talked
to anybody about--
- I've seen multiply doctors.

21:15.775 --> 21:18.609
Starting at the age of three,
I've been...

21:20.046 --> 21:23.047
called bipolar,
schizophrenic, delusional.

21:23.950 --> 21:26.183
I've been prescribed a dozen
different medications

21:26.185 --> 21:28.719
and 50 different cocktails.

21:29.222 --> 21:31.689
Some of them work
better than others.

21:32.492 --> 21:34.558
Some of them drowned it out.

21:42.468 --> 21:44.769
I can hear people's thoughts.

21:45.705 --> 21:46.971
- What about me?

21:46.972 --> 21:48.238
Can you hear what
I'm thinking right now?

21:48.241 --> 21:50.107
Can you hear my thoughts?

21:51.044 --> 21:53.577
- No, I can't hear
your thoughts.

21:53.579 --> 21:54.945
Um...

21:54.947 --> 21:56.747
It's part of why I like you.

21:56.749 --> 21:58.649
- Try.
Read my mind.

22:09.062 --> 22:10.828
- I can't.

22:10.830 --> 22:13.197
Just every now and then,
it doesn't happen very often,

22:13.199 --> 22:17.735
but it's like
they're blocked or...

22:17.737 --> 22:19.670
foggy somehow.

22:21.874 --> 22:24.141
[chuckles]
It's-- It's rare.

22:24.143 --> 22:28.546
Everyone else, it's like
a pool filled with red water.

22:29.282 --> 22:31.549
And I just fall in.

22:32.251 --> 22:33.851
- Can you show me?

22:36.122 --> 22:38.089
[whimsical music]

22:38.091 --> 22:40.157
¶¶

22:55.274 --> 22:57.308
- Ten o'clock, the girl
in the purple coat.

22:57.310 --> 22:59.009
See if you can hear her.

23:11.924 --> 23:14.592
[faint echoes]

23:29.175 --> 23:30.207
- Pregnant.

23:30.209 --> 23:32.109
She just found out
she's pregnant.

23:38.885 --> 23:39.950
- Excuse me,

23:39.952 --> 23:41.619
I'm conducting
a research study

23:41.621 --> 23:43.721
on women right
around your age.

23:43.723 --> 23:45.356
Sorry to intrude.

23:45.792 --> 23:49.760
Any chance that you...
may be pregnant?

23:53.733 --> 23:55.733
- I can't help you.

23:55.935 --> 23:57.601
- I'm sorry.

24:03.042 --> 24:04.341
[sighs]
I don't know.

24:04.343 --> 24:05.810
I mean, maybe you have
good intuition

24:05.812 --> 24:07.495
but are you reading
her mind?

24:07.496 --> 24:09.179
I don't know.
- She's also going
to meet her fiancé

24:09.182 --> 24:10.681
but she wants
to get drunk first

24:10.683 --> 24:12.783
because she feels guilty
for sleeping with her boss

24:12.785 --> 24:14.885
and doesn't know
whose kid it is.

24:18.090 --> 24:20.124
Why don't you ask her
about that?

24:22.795 --> 24:25.362
- [Dr. Deluce]<i> And this ability</i>
<i> is related to your blood.</i>

24:25.364 --> 24:28.165
Very rare blood type.
Correct?

24:29.268 --> 24:31.635
- Look, I know that you're
not inclined to believe me

24:31.637 --> 24:34.405
and I understand that a history
of mental health issues

24:34.407 --> 24:36.040
is relevant.

24:36.042 --> 24:37.842
The fact that
I was diagnosed

24:37.844 --> 24:39.243
with schizophrenia
in the past

24:39.245 --> 24:40.845
does not negate the fact

24:40.847 --> 24:43.747
that my baby was taken
ten days ago.

24:45.151 --> 24:48.853
- Sybil,
where are we right now?

24:48.855 --> 24:50.187
Look around.

24:50.923 --> 24:52.423
I need you to consider
the possibility

24:52.425 --> 24:54.225
that there are
other explanations

24:54.227 --> 24:56.994
for the voices you hear
and the images you see.

24:56.996 --> 24:58.863
- Of course, I mean,

24:58.865 --> 25:03.267
one explanation is that I'm
completely fucking insane.

25:03.269 --> 25:05.336
- Can you hear
my thoughts right now?

25:06.439 --> 25:08.672
- Take me off the meds.

25:10.776 --> 25:13.110
- David was supportive, right?
He believed you.

25:13.112 --> 25:15.045
- Yeah, I thought so.

25:17.383 --> 25:19.717
But something was wrong.

25:26.726 --> 25:28.559
It was the baby
talking to me.

25:32.465 --> 25:35.833
I mean, I don't know how
but that's what it was.

25:37.003 --> 25:39.837
I could hear it
and see what it saw.

25:39.839 --> 25:43.841
Not just a feeling
but literally hear and see it.

25:45.111 --> 25:47.177
We were connected.

25:48.414 --> 25:50.314
- What do you think
it wanted?

25:58.324 --> 26:00.224
- To warn me.

26:11.037 --> 26:13.270
[ghostly echoes]

26:18.978 --> 26:20.744
- [Dr. Deluce]<i> Tell me</i>
<i> about the trip.</i>

26:22.481 --> 26:24.748
<i> Tell me about the incident.</i>

26:34.060 --> 26:35.993
[whimsical music]

26:35.995 --> 26:38.362
¶¶

26:38.864 --> 26:41.265
