36:10.936 --> 36:13.403
- Yes, actually.

36:13.405 --> 36:15.805
- And what do you remember?

36:15.807 --> 36:18.708
The sound of their voice?
The light?

36:19.545 --> 36:20.944
Their breath?

36:22.748 --> 36:26.116
- Yes, most of that,
I suppose.

36:27.119 --> 36:29.085
It's a strong memory.

36:29.087 --> 36:30.987
If that's what
you're getting at.

36:34.893 --> 36:36.826
It was raining.

36:38.497 --> 36:41.364
I remember the rain
tickling my face.

36:43.135 --> 36:45.135
- Do you have kids?

36:47.706 --> 36:49.839
What's it like?

36:49.841 --> 36:51.508
- What's that?

36:53.545 --> 36:56.046
- Holding your baby
for the first time.

36:58.050 --> 37:00.717
- I think we should
stick with your therapy.

37:02.621 --> 37:04.120
- What's it like?

37:07.593 --> 37:09.993
- It's indescribable.

37:12.564 --> 37:14.164
- What do you remember?

37:19.671 --> 37:21.805
- He smelled sweet.

37:22.975 --> 37:25.041
Like cookie dough.

37:28.847 --> 37:31.481
- It's always the smells.

37:32.918 --> 37:35.185
Smells are our
strongest memories,

37:35.187 --> 37:37.687
don't you think?

37:43.829 --> 37:45.795
You're lucky.

37:49.768 --> 37:52.035
To have such a memory.

37:59.511 --> 38:01.711
It's not real.

38:04.116 --> 38:05.849
- I'm sorry?

38:05.851 --> 38:08.918
- Your brain
recreates that moment.

38:08.920 --> 38:11.154
Every time you remember it.

38:11.156 --> 38:14.658
You mind, literally, rebuilds
it all over again every time.

38:14.660 --> 38:16.526
Did you know that?

38:17.095 --> 38:19.195
- I did know that, yes.

38:19.197 --> 38:21.498
- So, every time you
remember your first kiss

38:21.500 --> 38:25.001
or the first time that you
held your baby it changes.

38:25.003 --> 38:28.805
It's like a painter
repainting the same scene

38:28.807 --> 38:32.742
over and over again
every time from scratch.

38:33.879 --> 38:36.046
- Okay, sure.

38:36.715 --> 38:40.483
- So, your first kiss
isn't really your first kiss.

38:40.485 --> 38:42.619
It's something else.

38:42.621 --> 38:45.855
It's your brain
rebuilding it.

38:45.857 --> 38:49.826
Every time just
a little less accurate.

38:52.597 --> 38:54.698
Maybe it was raining.

38:56.168 --> 38:58.268
Maybe it wasn't.

38:59.504 --> 39:02.806
Maybe your baby did
smell like cookie dough.

39:05.210 --> 39:07.377
Maybe it didn't even exist.

39:11.550 --> 39:15.752
If you think about it too much,
you'll stop trusting yourself.

39:15.754 --> 39:18.555
You won't believe any
of your memories anymore.

39:18.557 --> 39:20.190
Nothing.

39:23.895 --> 39:26.029
But what I am telling you.

39:28.533 --> 39:30.633
It's the truth.

39:30.635 --> 39:32.202
[thunder rumbling]

39:32.204 --> 39:34.237
It happened.

39:35.574 --> 39:37.540
- I have no doubt that
you have experienced

39:37.542 --> 39:40.643
real trauma, Sybil.

39:40.812 --> 39:43.580
Nothing is clearer to me
but what I am suggesting

39:43.582 --> 39:45.749
is that perhaps we need
to find some scenario--
- Don't patronize me.

39:45.751 --> 39:47.784
I'm telling the truth!

39:50.822 --> 39:53.590
- I think maybe we
should stop for today.

39:54.092 --> 39:55.759
- No.

39:56.027 --> 39:57.560
I want you to hear it.

39:57.561 --> 39:59.094
All of it and then I want you
to look me in the eyes

39:59.097 --> 40:02.332
and tell me
that you think I am lying!

