<i> I have to go.</i>

55:29.193 --> 55:31.226
-<i> Ma'am, it's okay.</i>

55:31.228 --> 55:32.828
- [Sybil]<i> No, I have to go.</i>

55:32.830 --> 55:34.897
-<i> Ma'am, I'm telling you,</i>
<i> you can't go anywhere</i>

55:34.899 --> 55:37.666
<i> unless me or another</i>
<i> nurse is with you.</i>

55:38.569 --> 55:40.536
You need to stay in bed
and get some rest.

55:40.538 --> 55:41.970
- What's going on here?

55:42.707 --> 55:43.939
- She got out of her bed

55:43.941 --> 55:45.974
and tore the IVs
out of her arm.

55:46.944 --> 55:49.111
- Well, if she wants to leave,
you gotta let her leave.

55:49.113 --> 55:50.713
Excuse me.

55:51.716 --> 55:53.582
- Who are you?
- I'm her physician.

55:53.584 --> 55:55.551
- And what exactly--

55:55.553 --> 55:58.087
- Has it been seven hours
between rotations?

55:58.089 --> 55:59.588
Is that some kind
of a joke?

55:59.590 --> 56:00.956
- I was on my way
down the hall.

56:00.958 --> 56:02.925
- Who prescribed
the magnesium sulphate?

56:02.927 --> 56:04.443
- Dr. Bleacher. I--

56:04.444 --> 56:05.960
- Are you trying to kill
this patient,

56:05.963 --> 56:06.979
is that what's
going on here?

56:06.980 --> 56:07.996
Because I look
at these dosages

56:07.998 --> 56:09.231
and all I can think
to myself

56:09.233 --> 56:11.200
is that you're trying
to kill her, Nurse...?

56:11.202 --> 56:12.835
- Hudson.
- Okay.

56:12.837 --> 56:14.837
This woman is coming with me,
alright?

56:14.839 --> 56:16.305
- I'm the floor manager.
What's going on?

56:16.307 --> 56:18.540
- Oh, good.
I am this woman's physician

56:18.542 --> 56:20.042
and she is leaving with me.

56:20.044 --> 56:22.077
- No, sir, I'm so sorry,
that is not possible.

56:22.079 --> 56:24.146
- I'm not gonna let her
spend one more second

56:24.148 --> 56:25.848
under this inept care,
okay?

56:25.850 --> 56:27.783
I will file the paperwork
on my way out to transfer.

56:27.785 --> 56:29.585
- I need proof
that you're a doctor.

56:29.587 --> 56:31.186
- Am I your physician?
- Yes.

56:31.188 --> 56:32.755
- Do you want me
to take you

56:32.757 --> 56:34.323
out of this hospital
immediately?

56:34.325 --> 56:35.758
- Yes.
Yes, I do.

56:35.760 --> 56:36.425
Yes.

56:36.427 --> 56:37.826
- That is patient consent.

56:37.828 --> 56:40.896
Now this woman has a history
of schizophrenia
- That being said...

56:40.898 --> 56:44.666
and you have had her done up
in here for eight hours!

56:44.668 --> 56:47.336
- Security!
- Keep going.
Go, go, go.

56:48.005 --> 56:49.772
- Security!

56:53.244 --> 56:55.043
- It's this way.
Come on.

57:02.286 --> 57:04.853
- Where are we going?
We need to go to the police.

57:06.023 --> 57:07.990
- We're not going
to the police.

57:09.860 --> 57:11.994
There's something
that you need to hear.

57:34.685 --> 57:38.987
There is a corollary
between your blood type

57:38.989 --> 57:41.089
and your abilities.

57:42.259 --> 57:44.159
You weren't the only one.

57:45.896 --> 57:48.063
Right now, I believe,

57:48.065 --> 57:50.232
that there is
a group of people

57:50.234 --> 57:53.068
and they have an enormous
amount of resources

57:53.070 --> 57:54.303
and they are very,

57:54.305 --> 57:57.206
very interested
in your blood type

57:57.208 --> 57:58.907
and the abilities
that it carries.

57:58.909 --> 58:03.312
And they are willing to kill
and kidnap to get it.

58:03.314 --> 58:08.150
Alright, now,
Katherine Warren knew this,

58:08.152 --> 58:09.985
Okay?

58:09.987 --> 58:11.920
I showed her the evidence,
alright?

58:11.922 --> 58:14.423
That's why she moved you
around from place to place.

58:14.425 --> 58:16.825
She was protecting you.

58:16.827 --> 58:19.127
You must have
picked up on this.

58:19.396 --> 58:21.697
Her death
was not an accident.

58:21.699 --> 58:22.931
They got to her.

58:22.933 --> 58:24.199
Just like they got to you

58:24.201 --> 58:27.169
and they're gonna keep
coming until it's done.

58:27.972 --> 58:30.806
Several months ago,
when you started seeing David,

58:30.808 --> 58:32.207
I dug into his background.

58:32.209 --> 58:34.376
Searched the public records
for David Holyfield

58:34.378 --> 58:36.045
and his family

58:36.046 --> 58:37.713
and I didn't find anything,
Sybil.

58:37.715 --> 58:39.381
How is that possible?

58:40.751 --> 58:42.951
Unless his identity is false.

58:42.953 --> 58:45.888
A week later they asked me
to resign at the hospital.

58:45.890 --> 58:47.856
And when I said no,
they simply fired me

58:47.858 --> 58:50.692
and the medical board
revoked my license.

58:50.694 --> 58:52.794
I don't think
that's a coincidence.

58:53.430 --> 58:54.897
Look,

58:55.933 --> 58:59.368
none of this changes
the facts, alright?

59:00.271 --> 59:01.970
You have to run.

59:03.107 --> 59:05.040
- They have my son.

59:05.042 --> 59:07.493
- You have to hide.

59:07.494 --> 59:09.945
You have to go as far from
here as you possibly can.
- I'm not gonna run!

59:14.285 --> 59:16.084
- Okay. Okay.

59:17.121 --> 59:19.421
You're right.
Alright?

59:19.423 --> 59:21.456
We'll get your baby back.

59:22.059 --> 59:24.259
But not now,
not like this.

59:24.261 --> 59:27.229
You need time to heal,
alright?

59:28.132 --> 59:30.732
You need to come up
with a strategy.

59:30.734 --> 59:33.001
Come up with a plan,
get off the grid.

59:33.003 --> 59:35.170
You know,
get off their radar.

59:35.171 --> 59:37.338
Give yourself time to collect
your strength, your wits.

59:41.812 --> 59:43.779
- Where?

59:54.158 --> 59:55.524
- What happened next?

59:56.460 --> 59:57.859
- You know what.

59:58.462 --> 1:00:00.929
He put me in this psych ward,
that's what.

1:00:05.369 --> 1:00:07.369
<i> At the time I thought</i>
<i> he was betraying me.</i>

1:00:07.371 --> 1:00:10.405
<i> That maybe he was even</i>
<i> one of them, but now...</i>

1:00:11.141 --> 1:00:13.408
<i> I know that he was just</i>
<i> trying to protect me.</i>

1:00:13.410 --> 1:00:15.177
<i> To get me somewhere safe.</i>

1:00:18.382 --> 1:00:20.733
Off the grid.

1:00:20.734 --> 1:00:23.085
He knew I needed to calm
down make rational plans.

1:00:23.087 --> 1:00:25.320
- So, you're off
the grid now then?

1:00:27.024 --> 1:00:28.957
- Not for long.

1:00:29.927 --> 1:00:31.960
- When you tried to make
contact with Dr Morales

1:00:31.962 --> 1:00:34.463
when you called him
from the hospital,

1:00:34.465 --> 1:00:36.031
what happened?

1:00:36.800 --> 1:00:39.401
- I called his cell phone,
not a working number.

1:00:39.970 --> 1:00:41.403
Called his house.

1:00:42.072 --> 1:00:44.072
Someone else answered.

1:00:44.074 --> 1:00:45.807
<i> Said I had</i>
<i> the wrong number.</i>

1:00:49.279 --> 1:00:51.546
But I know what happened.

1:01:04.228 --> 1:01:06.161
Okay, now I need
to know something.

1:01:06.163 --> 1:01:07.529
- What?

1:01:07.531 --> 1:01:09.398
- Are you gonna help me?

1:01:11.368 --> 1:01:13.568
Or are you gonna
keep me in this cage?

1:01:13.971 --> 1:01:16.405
- What would you do
if you were in my position?

1:01:17.141 --> 1:01:20.108
- I would help.
- Well, actually, it's my job.

1:01:20.110 --> 1:01:21.977
But I'm not
gonna bullshit you,

1:01:21.979 --> 1:01:23.412
most psychoanalysts
in my position

1:01:23.414 --> 1:01:26.181
wouldn't spend more than
ten minutes on your case.

1:01:26.183 --> 1:01:27.883
Highly intelligent female.

1:01:27.885 --> 1:01:29.518
Extreme early
childhood trauma.

1:01:29.520 --> 1:01:31.520
Extensive history
of mental illness,

1:01:31.522 --> 1:01:33.021
psychotic delusions.

1:01:33.023 --> 1:01:36.358
Lost her mother and then
her baby in the same year.

1:01:36.360 --> 1:01:38.593
Committed by her own
doctor because she claims,

1:01:38.595 --> 1:01:41.263
that her baby was taken
by an invisible cult

1:01:41.265 --> 1:01:42.864
because of her
ancient bloodline

1:01:42.866 --> 1:01:45.467
or her superhuman
ability to read minds.

1:01:46.336 --> 1:01:47.936
[bird chirps]

1:01:49.106 --> 1:01:51.139
Did you know that most patients
suffering from schizophrenia

1:01:51.141 --> 1:01:52.541
were born in the winter?

1:01:52.543 --> 1:01:54.209
Do you know that?

1:01:55.045 --> 1:01:57.145
When I learned that
I couldn't make sense of it

1:01:57.147 --> 1:02:00.148
but turns out that there is
a reasonable correlation.

1:02:00.150 --> 1:02:03.251
See that's when most
in utero infections occur,

1:02:03.253 --> 1:02:06.955
which then increases the
chance of disease in infants.

1:02:06.957 --> 1:02:09.257
We get sick in the winter more
than any other time of year

1:02:09.259 --> 1:02:11.493
and the same happens
for pregnant women

1:02:11.495 --> 1:02:14.429
and then their babies
have problems later on in life.

1:02:14.431 --> 1:02:17.899
Nothing the babies did
wrong or right,

1:02:17.901 --> 1:02:19.501
for that matter.

1:02:19.502 --> 1:02:21.102
Their mothers were just
pregnant during the winter.

1:02:21.105 --> 1:02:22.471
Plain and simple.

1:02:23.006 --> 1:02:24.673
My point is, Sybil,
this is not something

1:02:24.675 --> 1:02:27.642
that you chose
or you caused.

1:02:28.378 --> 1:02:31.279
Genetics and environment
conspired against you

1:02:31.281 --> 1:02:33.949
the same way they conspired
against 17 million

1:02:33.951 --> 1:02:36.551
other people on this planet
with your condition.

1:02:37.154 --> 1:02:38.987
- My condition?

1:02:40.124 --> 1:02:42.591
- You did not make
yourself sick.

1:02:42.593 --> 1:02:45.160
But with focus,
medication, planning,

1:02:45.162 --> 1:02:46.928
a strategy,

1:02:46.930 --> 1:02:48.997
you can make yourself well,

1:02:48.999 --> 1:02:51.399
function in a normal capacity.

1:02:52.169 --> 1:02:54.402
- Make myself well.

1:02:56.073 --> 1:02:58.173
- And that starts today

1:02:58.675 --> 1:03:00.075
if you want it.

1:03:00.077 --> 1:03:01.209
- If I want it.

1:03:01.211 --> 1:03:02.711
- Yeah.

1:03:05.983 --> 1:03:07.682
- Gotcha.

1:03:12.422 --> 1:03:15.557
You're not gonna believe me
no matter what I say.

1:03:16.493 --> 1:03:18.660
The only way out of here
is if I lie

1:03:18.662 --> 1:03:21.263
and tell you I'm nuts,
made the whole thing up

1:03:21.265 --> 1:03:24.966
to handle the trauma
and guilt of a stillborn.

1:03:28.005 --> 1:03:31.606
Okay, you win.

1:03:33.644 --> 1:03:36.178
I'm nothing.
I'm nobody.

1:03:36.713 --> 1:03:38.680
How could I even deserve
to have a child

1:03:38.682 --> 1:03:43.251
and be a mother,
have a family,

1:03:44.755 --> 1:03:46.454
to be normal?

1:03:48.458 --> 1:03:50.258
Of course I don't.

1:03:50.260 --> 1:03:53.094
Of course, I made the whole
thing up to process it,

1:03:53.096 --> 1:03:53.461
to bury it.

1:03:57.568 --> 1:04:00.535
Yeah, something like that,
would that do it for you people?

1:04:02.139 --> 1:04:05.674
- First of all, Sybil, what
happened was not your fault.

1:04:05.676 --> 1:04:09.344
And second, right now,
it's just you and me.

1:04:09.346 --> 1:04:11.213
Sybil, look at me.

1:04:12.249 --> 1:04:14.382
I am not they,
I'm not abstract,

1:04:14.384 --> 1:04:16.551
I'm just me.

1:04:16.553 --> 1:04:18.653
And I don't want you to lie.

1:04:18.655 --> 1:04:21.389
I want you
to find the truth.

1:04:21.391 --> 1:04:25.026
And I know you're scared
but it is okay to be scared.

1:04:28.165 --> 1:04:30.098
I understand

1:04:31.134 --> 1:04:33.301
'cos I lost my baby, too.

1:04:39.776 --> 1:04:41.643
- I know.

1:04:44.381 --> 1:04:46.815
- And I know you want
to hide behind this.

1:04:48.518 --> 1:04:50.585
- This is different.

1:04:53.557 --> 1:04:57.259
I know you don't believe me
but this really happened.

1:04:58.395 --> 1:05:00.729
It's real.
- Yes.

1:05:00.731 --> 1:05:02.497
You had a caesarean.

1:05:02.499 --> 1:05:04.833
The procedure was done
at St John's Hospital.

1:05:04.835 --> 1:05:06.768
I have the medical records.

1:05:06.770 --> 1:05:08.203
- From where?

1:05:08.205 --> 1:05:10.572
- Dr. Morales
had them released

1:05:10.574 --> 1:05:11.606
the night
you were discharged.

1:05:11.608 --> 1:05:13.575
- Those are not real.

1:05:14.411 --> 1:05:15.644
I was never discharged.

1:05:15.646 --> 1:05:18.079
He fabricated them.
He falsified signatures.

1:05:18.081 --> 1:05:18.980
- Why, Sybil?

1:05:18.982 --> 1:05:20.749
Why would he do that?
- To protect me!

1:05:24.521 --> 1:05:26.554
What do the records say?

1:05:27.324 --> 1:05:30.191
- According to the records...

1:05:32.796 --> 1:05:34.596
- Say it.

1:05:37.634 --> 1:05:39.834
- Sybil, your baby died.

1:05:43.640 --> 1:05:45.774
Right after childbirth.

1:05:50.547 --> 1:05:52.614
[bird flutters/chirps]

1:05:57.788 --> 1:06:00.288
- But I could see it.

1:06:01.825 --> 1:06:04.392
<i> I could see the room where</i>
<i> they were keeping him.</i>

1:06:04.394 --> 1:06:05.844
<i> I could see it.</i>

1:06:05.845 --> 1:06:07.295
- [Dr. Deluce]<i> And where</i>
<i> would that be?</i>

1:06:08.365 --> 1:06:10.832
Sybil, you want to believe
that your baby is still alive

1:06:10.834 --> 1:06:12.801
but the truth.

1:06:12.803 --> 1:06:14.369
What frightens you more

1:06:14.371 --> 1:06:16.271
than the horrifying
events of your story

1:06:16.273 --> 1:06:18.506
is the idea that they
never even happened.

1:06:18.508 --> 1:06:21.643
That the Holyfield family is
just a construct in your mind.
- No, no.

1:06:21.645 --> 1:06:24.879
- That David never
came back that morning.

1:06:24.881 --> 1:06:26.648
Sybil, we checked.

1:06:29.853 --> 1:06:32.754
<i> David Holyfield</i>
<i> does not exist.</i>

1:06:32.756 --> 1:06:34.456
[sobbing]
- No!

1:06:34.925 --> 1:06:37.459
- [Dr. Deluce]<i> Someone went home</i>
<i> with you that night.</i>

1:06:38.762 --> 1:06:40.795
<i> And you had intercourse</i>
<i> and you got pregnant</i>

1:06:40.797 --> 1:06:43.531
<i> but you never saw</i>
<i> the man again, Sybil.</i>

1:06:46.370 --> 1:06:47.836
I even Google Mapped it.

1:06:47.838 --> 1:06:50.271
There is no structure
the size of the house

1:06:50.273 --> 1:06:51.573
you're describing
in that area.

1:06:51.575 --> 1:06:53.641
It's all national forest.

1:06:53.643 --> 1:06:55.510
That's what our mind
does to protect us.

1:06:55.512 --> 1:06:58.480
It creates these fantasies,
these delusions

1:06:58.482 --> 1:07:00.548
and they're wrapped
one inside the other.

1:07:00.550 --> 1:07:02.500
Everything you have told me,

1:07:02.501 --> 1:07:04.451
<i> the man and the road</i>
<i> and the ancient house</i>

1:07:04.454 --> 1:07:06.554
<i> and the labyrinth</i>
<i> and the all-seeing eye.</i>

1:07:06.556 --> 1:07:08.690
<i> The mother and child,</i>
<i> the chosen one.</i>

1:07:08.692 --> 1:07:11.192
<i> Sybil, they are fragments.</i>

1:07:11.194 --> 1:07:13.661
<i> They are building blocks</i>
<i> of our collective unconscious.</i>

1:07:13.663 --> 1:07:15.196
These things belong
to all of us

1:07:15.198 --> 1:07:16.464
but the details
that you gave me,

1:07:16.466 --> 1:07:17.832
that is your creation
to help you

1:07:17.834 --> 1:07:19.834
because that is how
the mind works.

1:07:19.836 --> 1:07:23.271
That's its job,
that's how it processes trauma.

1:07:23.273 --> 1:07:25.707
And it doesn't mean to hurt us,
it's trying to help.

1:07:25.709 --> 1:07:28.576
And it does, sometimes,
it does for a while,

1:07:28.578 --> 1:07:29.944
it gets us through it,
it helps us deal

1:07:29.946 --> 1:07:33.748
but there comes a time
when you have got to wake up.

1:07:33.750 --> 1:07:36.518
You have got to face the truth
and it doesn't happen overnight

1:07:36.520 --> 1:07:37.852
but I am here.

1:07:37.854 --> 1:07:39.454
I am here,
I will help you through,

1:07:39.456 --> 1:07:41.356
I will help you to face it

1:07:41.357 --> 1:07:43.257
but, Sybil, I have got to know
that you're here with me.

1:07:43.860 --> 1:07:46.561
Are you here with me,
Sybil?

1:07:48.765 --> 1:07:50.832
- I'm scared.

1:07:51.835 --> 1:07:57.705
- Sybil, do not confuse
fear with sickness.

1:07:57.707 --> 1:07:59.808
I know you're scared,
it's okay to be scared.

1:07:59.810 --> 1:08:02.944
Everybody is scared.
You just need time.

1:08:06.483 --> 1:08:08.583
[cries]
- [Sybil]<i> My baby.</i>

1:08:10.387 --> 1:08:12.253
My baby.

1:08:12.255 --> 1:08:13.688
[whispered]
- It's okay.

1:08:14.391 --> 1:08:15.957
[whispered]
It's okay.

1:08:17.494 --> 1:08:19.461
[whispered]
I'm so sorry.

1:08:19.896 --> 1:08:21.896
I'm so sorry.

1:08:33.343 --> 1:08:34.876
[bird chirps]

1:08:36.580 --> 1:08:37.745
[Dr. Deluce]<i> The patient</i>
<i> is alert,</i>

1:08:37.747 --> 1:08:39.881
<i> oriented and responsive.</i>

1:08:39.883 --> 1:08:42.984
<i> She's able to differentiate</i>
<i> her perceptual disturbances</i>

1:08:42.986 --> 1:08:45.237
<i> from reality</i>

1:08:45.238 --> 1:08:47.489
<i> and is no longer reacting</i>
<i> to internal stimuli.</i>

1:08:47.491 --> 1:08:49.591
<i> And has demonstrated</i>
<i> a willingness</i>

1:08:49.593 --> 1:08:51.659
<i> to follow the specific</i>
<i> guidelines</i>

1:08:51.661 --> 1:08:54.429
<i> of continued medication</i>
<i> and therapy.</i>

1:08:54.431 --> 1:08:55.797
- [man 1]<i> So, she's not</i>
<i> dangerous?</i>

1:08:55.799 --> 1:08:57.299
- [Dr. Deluce]<i> No.</i>

1:08:57.300 --> 1:08:58.800
- [man 2]<i> Miss Warren, do you</i>
<i> understand the guidelines</i>

1:08:58.802 --> 1:09:01.870
<i> and your obligations</i>
<i> once you're released?</i>

1:09:02.706 --> 1:09:04.472
- Yes,

1:09:04.474 --> 1:09:06.574
I know what
needs to be done.

1:09:13.884 --> 1:09:17.018
[music box plays lullaby]
¶¶

1:09:17.420 --> 1:09:19.454
[baby cooing]

1:09:30.767 --> 1:09:32.433
[train horn sounding]

1:09:33.970 --> 1:09:35.970
[dramatic music builds]

1:09:35.972 --> 1:09:37.972
¶¶

1:09:58.461 --> 1:10:00.528
[grunts in effort]

1:10:14.477 --> 1:10:16.477
[gun magazine clicks]

1:10:16.479 --> 1:10:17.946
- Now,

